  "body": "F0/F3/F4 shipped cleanly; Director re-prioritized Phase F resume around an org-chart visualization (the 'Available positions' flat list shows what's claimable, but a chart shows the structure — reports_to chains, peer / validates_for / coordinates_with edges, who reports to whom). New top priority: F-chart (org-chart display in the panel, per-org, with live-state overlay for vacant/claimed). F1 memo browser + F2 compose from panel slide behind F-chart. F5 mirror-list deferred (no fixtures carry x.org.org_location data); vacate-binding parked (no cross-account claim signal yet); cross-spec canonical-JSON coordination on hold pending orgdef-strategist signal. No new MCP tools or schema changes; pure panel-side work; rendering tech is engineer's call. body_ref has full scope, acceptance criteria, render.catdef.org coordination note, what NOT to do.",
